OL,3,C'I used to abuse my wife - this is how
OL,4,CI changed my ways'
OL,6,FWalking on eggshells, unsure of what
OL,7,Fshe had 'done' and living in fear of
OL,8,Fwhat might happen next.
OL,10,FThose were constant feelings for
OL,11,FAlison, not her real name, in her
OL,12,Fmarriage.
OL,14,FHer husband Pete, also not his real
OL,15,Fname, would often be shouting in their
OL,16,Fmarital home in Gloucestershire.
OL,18,FHe would verbally abuse her, leaving
OL,19,Fher feeling frightened as he stomped
OL,20,Faround the house and slammed doors and
OL,21,Fcupboards as he went.
