OL,3,C'I used to abuse my wife - this is how
OL,4,CI changed my ways'
OL,6,F"For no apparent reason I felt like I
OL,7,Fwas a victim but I didn't know what I
OL,8,Fhad done or what was coming. I never
OL,9,Fknew how it was going to escalate.
OL,11,F"Over the first 10 weeks (of the
OL,12,Fcourse) he'd open the door to
OL,13,Fconversation. He'd listen when I'd say
OL,14,F'can you unclench your first' or 'you
OL,15,Fdon't need to shut the cupboard door
OL,16,Flike that, you're making me jumpy'.
